metadata.title: Mooney M20
aws::graph::propositions: Mooney M20 Aircraft Specifications and History
Gross weight of Mooney M20 was reduced to 2,500 lb (1,100 kg).
Mooney M20 was certified on October 15, 1962.
161 total Mooney M20 aircraft were built.
100 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1963.
51 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1964.
9 Mooney M20 aircraft were built in 1965.
1 Mooney M20 aircraft was built in 1966.
M20E is a model of Mooney M20.
M20E Super 21 was introduced in 1964.
M20E Super 21 is a higher-powered version of the Mark 21.
M20E is powered by a fuel injected 200 hp (150 kW) Lycoming IO-360-A1A engine.
M20E is largely identical to the M20C except for the engine.
M20E received the "positive control" autopilot system in 1965.
M20C received the "positive control" autopilot system in 1965.
A retractable entrance step was introduced to M20E in 1965.
Improved nose gear door closures were introduced to M20E in 1965.
New bucket seats with recessed arm rests were introduced to M20E in 1965.
Improved cabin ventilation was introduced to M20E in 1965.
A ram air power boost to improve high altitude performance was introduced to M20E in 1965.
Electrically retracting landing gear was introduced as an option for M20E in 1965.

text:
Gross weight was reduced to 2,500 lb (1,100 kg).  Certified October 15, 1962.  161 total built; 100 (1963), 51 (1964), 9 (1965), and 1 (1966).
M20E

M20E Super 21, introduced in 1964 as a higher-powered version of the Mark 21.  Powered by a fuel injected 200 hp (150 kW) Lycoming IO-360-A1A engine, the M20E is otherwise largely identical to the M20C.  Like the M20C, the M20E received the "positive control" autopilot system in 1965.  Other changes introduced in 1965 include a retractable entrance step, improved nose gear door closures, new bucket seats with recessed arm rests, improved cabin ventilation, a ram air power boost to improve high altitude performance, and optional electrically retracting landing gear.
